1.5 Brand Voice

Every article should sound like an experienced engineer explaining a project to a colleague.

The tone should be:

Professional.

Encouraging.

Helpful.

Confident.

Calm.

Avoid:

excessive enthusiasm
unnecessary adjectives
exaggerated claims
marketing language
clickbait

Good:

Connect the SDA pin to GPIO21 because this is the default I2C data pin on most ESP32 development boards.

Avoid:

This AMAZING feature will completely REVOLUTIONIZE your project!

1.6 Writing Style

Use:

Short paragraphs.

Clear sentences.

Logical flow.

Simple technical language.

Explain new concepts before using them.

Avoid repeating information.

Every section should have a purpose.

1.7 Visual Identity

The visual identity must be instantly recognizable.

Every article should share:

identical typography
identical spacing
identical image style
identical color palette
identical diagrams
identical logo placement

Consistency is more important than originality.

1.8 Logo Usage

Only the official Embedded Nerd logo may be used.

Rules:

Never redraw the logo.
Never recreate it using AI.
Never distort proportions.
Never rotate it.
Never stretch it.
Never change colors.
Never add effects.

Always maintain sufficient white space around the logo.

1.9 Logo Placement

Default position:

Top-right corner.

The logo should appear on:

Hero images
Wiring diagrams
Pinout diagrams
Flow diagrams
Finished project images
Comparison graphics

Do not place the logo in the center of an image.

Do not cover important content.

