Comfortable line spacing.

Consistent hierarchy.

Never mix multiple font families.

1.13 Heading Hierarchy

H1

Only once.

H2

Main sections.

H3

Subsections.

H4

Only when necessary.

Never skip heading levels.

1.14 White Space

Always leave generous spacing between:

headings
images
tables
code blocks
paragraphs

Crowded pages reduce readability.

1.15 Icons

Use simple line icons when appropriate.

Avoid:

emoji overload
decorative graphics
inconsistent icon styles

Icons should support understanding rather than decoration.

1.16 Tables

Tables should always be:

Simple.

Readable.

Consistent.

Example:

Component	Quantity
