Avoid overly complex tables.

1.17 Diagrams

Every diagram should:

Use rounded corners.

Use consistent colors.

Use consistent spacing.

Use professional typography.

Contain only necessary information.

Readers should understand the diagram within a few seconds.

1.18 Image Consistency

Every image generated for Embedded Nerd should appear to belong to the same visual family.

Maintain:

identical perspective
identical shadows
identical typography
identical lighting
identical color palette
identical margins
identical logo placement

No image should feel visually different from the rest of the website.

1.19 Branding in Images

Every original illustration should include:

Official Embedded Nerd logo.

EmbeddedNerd.com.

Subtle branding.

Branding should never distract from the educational content.

1.20 Professional Standards

Readers should immediately recognize three characteristics:

Accuracy

Information is technically correct.

Clarity

Information is easy to understand.

Consistency

Everything follows the same visual and editorial standards.

1.21 Trust

Trust is the most valuable asset of Embedded Nerd.

Never sacrifice trust for:

SEO
affiliate revenue
publication speed
marketing

Every decision should prioritize the reader.

1.22 Long-Term Identity

The visual identity should remain stable over time.

Small improvements are encouraged.

Frequent redesigns are discouraged.

Readers should recognize Embedded Nerd even years later.

1.23 Brand Signature

Every tutorial should leave readers with the impression that it was created with care, precision, and genuine expertise.

The Embedded Nerd brand should become synonymous with:

High-quality embedded systems tutorials
Reliable source code
Clear diagrams
Professional presentation
Practical learning
Long-term educational value
